Title: Seiko SNJ009 Titanium Digital/Analogue. H023-00D0. Circa August 2005. VERY RARE!
Description: Seiko H023-00D0SNJ009 Up for grabs is another incredibly rare Seiko sports watch.This is the H023 based digital analogue (later to be moved to the Sportura range).It is a scarce watch in steel, but in titanium they almost never come up for sale - this is the first I've handled. This one dates to 2005, and the RRP at the time was an eye-watering £400! CASE:Titanium case.41mm diameter, 12mm deep.Buttons at 2, 4, 8 and 10 positions.Mineral glass. BRACELET:Titanium, Seiko reference 3295-G-IIntegrated fitting.Fold over locking clasp with push button release.Fits a 7.5" wrist and there are TEN removable links fitted. DIAL:Black dial with white detail.The whole of the base dial is a three-line digital display.Chapter ring has 28 cities for the "world time" function.Analogue hands in the centre - second, minute and hour hands. The digital lay-out shows the function at the top (time, alarm, world time, chronograph) andtwo lines for the display at the bottom. In time mode it shows day, date and the time in digital form. MOVEMENT:Super advanced H023 calibre.Digital display with analogue hands.New battery fitted, perfect working perfectly. CONDITION:Good. The case and bracelet show general light marks due to age.The glass has a couple of light scratches on the left side to centre.Full working order, all functions work as they should. This is a really nice watch for a collector to pick up. The steel ones pop up from time to time but the Ti models have become real collectors items! Thanks for looking.
